      <entry xml:id="entry_o_1" xml:lang="os" abv:completeness="incomplete">
        <?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20211017T182410+0300" comment="o (ho) - не знаю, куда деть скобки
"?>
        <form type="lemma"><orth>o</orth></form><?oxy_comment_end?>
        <sense><?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20211017T174904+0300" comment="пока не знаю, куда это девать"?>утвердительная частица,<?oxy_comment_end?>
          <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>да</q>
          </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
            <q>yes</q>
          </abv:tr></sense>
        <exampleGrp xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">aftæ ū?— o</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">так ли это? — да</q>
            </tr>
            <tr xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">is ti so? — yes</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
              <ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/>
              <biblScope>28</biblScope>
            </bibl>
          </example>
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">„о“ k˳y
              zæ<?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20211017T175410+0300" comment="тут должно быть что-то над g?"?>g<?oxy_comment_end?>aj,
              wæd Lakatīmæ baxæstæg kængystæm, „пæ“ — wæd ta næ alḱī jæ færnyg xæʒarmæ
              acæwʒæn</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">если ты скажешь «да», то мы
                породнимся с Лакаевыми, (если) «нет», то каждый из нас отправится в
                свой благословенный дом</q>
            </tr>
            <tr xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">if you say 'yes', then we will
                become related to the Lakayevs, (if) 'no', then each of us will go
                to his blessed home</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
              <?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20211017T175714+0300" comment="У Абаева там же вместо ссылки"?><ref
                type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><?oxy_comment_end?>
              <biblScope>28</biblScope>
            </bibl>
          </example>
          <example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
            <usg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><lang/></usg>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ho, xezuncæ пæ ragæj</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">да, они ждут нас давно</q>
            </tr>
            <tr xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">yes, they have been waiting for
                us for a while</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
              <ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/>
              <biblScope>72</biblScope>
            </bibl>
          </example>
          <example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
            <usg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><lang/></usg>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ho-ho, пæ ʒori rædudæj</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">да-да, ты не ошибаешься</q>
            </tr>
            <tr xml:lang="en">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">yes-yes, you are not wrong</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
              <ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/>
              <biblScope>72</biblScope>
            </bibl>
          </example>
        </exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Видимо, не связано с какой-либо одной языковой традицией; ср., с
          одной стороны, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang xml:lang="fa"
          /><w>hā</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tg"><lang xml:lang="tg"
          /><w>ho</w><gloss><q>да</q></gloss></mentioned>, с другой — <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"
            ><lang/><w>ho</w><gloss><q>да</q></gloss></mentioned>(<bibl><ref
              type="bibl" target="#ref_Груз. сл."/><biblScope>VIII
                1645</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">It is not apparently associated with one language tradition;
          cf., on one side, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang xml:lang="fa"
          /><w>hā</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tg"><lang xml:lang="tg"
          /><w>ho</w><gloss><q>yes</q></gloss></mentioned>, on the other —
          <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
            ><lang/><w>ho</w><gloss><q>yes</q></gloss></mentioned>(<bibl><ref
              type="bibl" target="#ref_Груз. сл."/><biblScope>VIII
                1645</biblScope></bibl>).</etym>
      </entry>
